article.headline: Loyola, Md. 83, Siena 76
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Loyola players hit all but one shot from the floor and were perfect from the foul line in overtime to beat Siena 83-76 on Saturday in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference. Michael Tuck had 15 points and 11 rebounds for the Greyhounds (15-12, 10-5), while Brett Harvey scored 19 points and Brian Rudolph added 15 points and 8 boards. The teams were tied at the end of the first half 32-32 and at the end of regulation 66-66. But Loyola shot 4-for-5 in the extra period and 8-for-8 from the foul line, while the Saints made only three of 10 baskets and three of four foul shots. Edwin Ubiles scored career-high 37 points for Siena (16-9, 11-4). Josh Duell had 11 points and Kenny Hasbrouck had 10.
